                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/711.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-05-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 5, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The President was legally elected, order prevails and the members of the Cabinet
                    seem to be favorably disposed towards American influence. Instruction desired in
                    regard to recognition.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Furniss</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
